T1  - COMPETITIVE EQUILIBRIA IN MATCHING MODELS WITH FINANCIAL CONSTRAINTS
AU  - Herings, P. Jean-Jacques
AU  - Zhou, Yu
Y1  - 2022/05/01
PY  - 2022
DA  - 2022/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12550
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
JA  - International Economic Review
SP  - 777
EP  - 802
VL  - 63
IS  - 2
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12550
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract We consider a matching with contracts model in which buyers face financial constraints. In this model, a competitive equilibrium may fail to exist. We therefore propose the new notion of quantity-constrained competitive equilibrium (QCCE). At a QCCE, buyers form expectations about the expected supply of trades. A buyer may expect that a trade is not to be supplied if the corresponding financial constraint is binding. We show the existence of QCCEs via a dynamic process that updates prices and quantity constraints, the equivalence between QCCE outcomes and stable outcomes, and some other properties of QCCEs like the lattice property.
ER  - 

